In this private, gated agricultural subdivision in Haiku lies a 1.26 acre parcel that’s ready to build a main home. Build site has both beautiful North Shore ocean and lush green valley views. Subdivision has private water system, this allows you to build the home you desire, and not restricted by fixture count. This is the main home portion of a two lot CPR.

2.287 Luscious Acres of Nature. Secluded and very private just off of West Kuiaha.This unit has a plantation style dwelling built in 1920. Unit E is part of a Condominium Property Regime; Kuiaha Pauwela Condominium.The dwelling needs TLC, now currently occupied and could be lived in.The structure's condition would not qualify for standard mortgages. Cash will be the answer to owning this property with all it's potential. Tax records reflect a 1043 sq-ft 3 bed 1 bath structure.With the structure being built prior to 1950, there may not be any building permit records on file. ***Please do not access any of these Condominium Properties without being accompanied by your Agent and Listing Agent.*** Call for an appointment to view. Easily shown

Classic plantation home newly painted and upgraded with tropical setting and great living. This CPR'd property is gated and private with 555 sq ft (county records show 616 sq ft.)with an additional 182 sq ft enclosed garage/storage and new deck of 220 sq ft. The property is 8,915 sq ft adjacent to common area that can be used for parking or extra outdoor space. Upgrades include new electrical wiring and plumbing. Near Hanzawa Store this parcel is level and great for outdoor entertaining or gardening.

Two acres of pristine beauty in Haiku, level, quiet and private. The lot is cleared of trees in the interior of lot and is lined with trees on two sides. Property is within 3 minutes of Hana Hwy. So close yet so far. Property features WATER METER, electric, cable and phone available at street. This property is a gem, don’t miss this one.

Located at Door of Faith Rd, this vacant lot offers many opportunities to build your private retreat, farm, or grow tropical fruits and plants all on 3.3 acres. In the past, part of the lot has been used to raise Taro and many varieties of tropical foliage. A small stream runs through the back end of property. Buyer to install water catchment.

A great deal in Haiku with full utilities and an ocean view. Lot has just been cleared and has good access via new driveway. Water meter and overhead power located on lot, great head start for any future structures. You can't see the lot from the street, you have to drive in at the top at new driveway. Private and secluded, yet 10 minutes to Hanzawas General Store and Haiku Marketplace. Zoned for large house and 1000 sq. ft. accessory dwelling and barns. Great lot for horses and livestock if you like critters.If you love trees, this place is for you.

Your opportunity to own the perfect starter home or downsized residence in the heart of Haiku town is as ripe as the tangerines in the front yard. Built in 2005 by a local contractor who exudes innovative design along with high quality and custom craftsmanship in everything that he does, 784 Kihau demonstrates pride of ownership in every respect. The 25 ft. open beam ceilings invite natural light, warmth, and enhance the sense of space. Varied and tasteful custom woodwork throughout. There is a bedroom on the ground floor in addition to the interior loft sleeping area on the second floor (fit for a king bed.) The owned solar PV system in place equates to lower utility bills in addition to the ridiculously low property taxes. Hang out or play hide and go seek in the tranquil outdoor loft space above the carport parking area. The yard is almost entirely fenced- the grass is lush, the citrus fruit is outstanding, and the tropical flowers smell sweet and bring smiles to all. The 240 sq.ft. exterior deck is perfect for talking story or moonlight dining under the stars. This home is as cozy as they come in Haiku and is priced for an immediate sale. First showings to be conducted Saturday and Sunday 2/20-2/21 from 11 am to 2 pm with a previously scheduled appointment.

Located at the end of W. Lelehuna Place you will find this 9,019 sq.ft. spacious lot. The lawn is well kept and there's ample room to expand the existing home. The property overlooks the Haiku Elementary School and the Haiku Community Center. This 4 bedroom, 2 bath house is in need of some repairs. Mainly the master bathroom was torn out to make way for a new tub and toilet. The fixtures are there but the job is incomplete. The kitchen needs help with drawers missing the facing etc. The overall condition of the kitchen is poor. For a skilled person the improvements could easily be done. Cosmetically the entire house needs painting inside & out and it needs new flooring. The Property to be sold "as is". This is a short sale. Subject to Lien Holders approval.

Completely remodeled Home close to Haiku Town and shops. Low maintenance yard. Bonus detached workshop. One of the best Values in Haiku for a move-in ready home. Priced to sell. Won't last long. Actual square footage may not match county records.

Gorgeous 2 acre lot that's cleared on the interior and ready for your new home. This lot is very private and the perimeter of the property is surrounded by trees and natural vegetation. There's an old portuguese oven thats still standing from an old dwelling that used to be there. The general area is not tied in to county water so a catchment system will be needed. The lot is partially fenced and has a gated entry. Contact your local Realtor for more information or to view the property.

Scenic, private, quiet; conveniently located north-shore three plus acres o rolling land with large heritage trees- perfect for residential agricultural estate and growing grounds. Ocean and mountain views (with selective clearing). Location at Hana Highway and Lower Ulumalu Road with access from paved Ulumalu Rd. Distances: 30 minutes to Kahului airport; 15 minutes to Pa'ia Town, close catchment with Maui County upcountry water service applied for.

PRICE REDUCTION....Charming well-kept home nestled in community-like setting near Haiku School in the Hale Pilialoha neighborhood. This one level three bedroom one bath house has recently been painted for a fresh look, new laminate flooring through out the living room, dining and hall, windows have been up graded to vynal there is room to extend the home. The back yard has privacy and is well over 7,000 sf and has an area for BBQ's, gardening, hanging out, nicely terraced and has mature plants and trees. Two car garage has a storage room, and laundry room with full size washer and dryer and garage door. Close to shopping and world class dining and Ho'okipa a famous beach and surf spot.

Awesome location, super close to Hookipa and Jaws. Are you a surf junkie? This might be the perfect property for YOU! Located between two of the best surf spots on earth, this sturdy home awaits your personal touches. Fenced yard, fruit trees and tropical setting are close to everything on the North Shore. Hollow tile construction provides solid first floor walls. Check with an engineer about building a second story to capture more of the Trade Winds & view. Set among large lots, this property feels bigger than it is due to all the wild, undeveloped land around it. Large two car carport and storage areas, give plenty of space to hold all your water sport toys. Already charming, with a little elbow grease, this home could be a real show stopper! Call your favorite Realtor today so you don't miss out on the only free standing non CPR home in Haiku under $500,000.

Offering the best of both worlds, country living with close proximity to shopping, dining and many of Maui's finest schools! Located 2 miles from Makawao Town and just a tad further to Seabury Hall and Montessori School of Maui, this level 2.198 acre parcel is perfect for Goldilocks. Here, the climate is not too hot, not too cold, not too wet, not too dry...just right! Elevated at approximately 1,000' above sea level, near the junction of Kaupakalua and Kauhikoa Road, this parcel offers an abundance of mature trees providing both shade and privacy from the road. Pick your home site and enjoy views of the blue Pacific, Haleakala and West Maui Mountains. No CC&Rs and HOA fees.

Own breathtaking oceanfront property at a fraction of the cost! Enjoy 2 acres of 21.3 acres along Maui's beautiful North shore. Down a private country road, with unobstructed ocean views in from and nature surrounding the rest, this property offers privacy and serenity. The lovely post and pier home with an open floor plan, vaulted ceilings and lots of windows contributes to a relaxing home environment. This home is self-sufficient, featuring a solar electrical system and private water catchment. The property is also excellent for planting, growing or gardening and already is lush with avocado, strawberry guava, coconut and banana trees, among others. Fall in love with oceanfront living and surround yourself with the best Maui has to offer. Seller financing is available. Shown by appointment only. Do not disturb tenant.
The Maui Real Estate Team, Inc

Awesome Kailua lot with a stream and small water fall. There are two excellent building spots one with a gorgeous view and another that is more secluded. Less than 35 minutes to the airport and a convenient drive to the shops and restaurants of Paia, Hookipa Beach park, Haiku and Makawao! Telephone and Electric are available, off the grid living is certainly an option. Water will be by catchment. This lot offers a rare opportunity for an adventurous spirit.
The Maui Real Estate Team, Inc

This is 3.8 acres of stunning land in Haiku. For those that want to get back to nature, start a small farm or just enjoy the quiet of the Maui countryside, look no further. The lot is situated at the end of a road bordering EMI land. It has been grazed by cattle for many years. The lot is almost all usable with just enough slope to make the ocean views that much more impressive. Water is to be provided by catchment. Produce your own electricity via the sun. This is one of the best opportunities on the market for buyers who want to live simply amidst the natural beauty of Maui’s North Shore.

Watch the waves breaking at Kuiaha Bay from this secluded 10.35 acre ocean view property, just minutes from Hookipa Beach, Hana Highway, & Haiku School on Maui’s North Shore. There is a perfect home-site near the gated entrance with an unobstructed ocean view, county water, & power. Down a rugged jungle road, multiple acres have been cleared for agriculture &/or building opportunities. In the flourishing gulch, prolific 75 year-old lychee trees dot the landscape. You will also find avocado, mango, lilikoi, coffee, rollinia, coconut palms, black bamboo, & edible bamboo shoots - all growing alongside a seasonal stream. Numerous areas for meditation bungalows & ag structures are available, or enjoy the private forest just to wander. Raise specialty livestock or boutique crops in this unique gulch, protected from Maui’s trade winds. Bring your walking shoes to see all the wonderful potential here!

Home needs some TLC, but if you are looking for a private parcel and a contractors dream property you have found it! This is a Short Sale.
